==English==

===Etymology===
Verb form related to ''[[calf]]''

===Verb===
'''calve'''; intransitive
# To give [[birth]].
# (''figuratively'') Especially of an [[iceberg]], [[glacier]], etc. to break off or shed a large piece.
#: "The sea was dangerous because of icebergs '''calving''' off the nearby glacier."

